A 2014 study led by Kaptchuk consisted of one experimental¬† group taking a migraine drug labeled with the drug's name,another took a placebo labeled "placeboüíä," and a third group took nothingüôÖüèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è. The researchers discovered that the placebo üíäwas 50% as effective as the real drug to reduce pain after a migraine attackü§ï

You would think that it is probably because the subjects did not know it was a placebo üíäbut there is more research üìäthat shows the same results when subjects were aware there was a fake pill given. The regions in the subjects brainsüß† showed a change in activity which is so interesting! Same goes for the sham treatment where the patients were under the impression that they were going under surgery and in reality it was just the motions that were being performed and the patients pain lessened after the "procedure".¬†

Taking medicine or utilizing herbal remedies normally gives us healing effects, üßòtherefore, this experiment shows the power of associations that our brain makes and how it generalizes them across the board. Our mind body connection is so deep and so powerful, being aware of our beliefs and our intentions gives us the power to self heal in the most incredible ways!ü§ó

